d, more creative, more innovative, and above all, a better global citizen. Throughout, his commitment to and affection for Yale shines through.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEducation, HigherxAims and objectiveszUnited States. 0aEducation, HigherxPhilosophy. 0aUniversities and colleges. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030019851540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300198515423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300198515/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles